  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Research and capacity-building in communities affected by mining to create alternatives to development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Red Muqui is a Peruvian civil society coalition working on the social impact of mining. It has 27 members, including key CAFOD partner CEAS, the Social Action Commission of the Peruvian Bishops&#x2019; Conference and ten other Church-based groups. The project aims to enable communities and populations living in mining areas to coordinate and strengthen their capacities to defend their individual and collective rights. It also seeks to promote alternatives to extractive industries and to influence regional, local and community development processes through an economic model based on sustainability and &apos;buen vivir&apos;.</narrative>
  </description>
